{"parse":{"title":"Great Daffodil Appeal","pageid":43298351,"revid":827210407,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>The Great Daffodil Appeal</b> is <a href=\"/wiki/Marie_Curie_(Charity)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marie Curie (Charity)\">Marie Curie</a>'s biggest annual fundraising campaign.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Every March, millions of people across the UK support this fundraising event by giving a small donation to wear a daffodil pin. This makes it one of the UK\u2019s most recognisable charity appeals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Money raised through the appeal helps Marie Curie provide free care and support to people living with a terminal illnesses.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Key_facts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Key facts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Celebrity_supporters\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Celebrity supporters</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Daffodil_Appeal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first Great Daffodil Appeal took place in 1986 with volunteers collecting donations and handing out fresh daffodils.\n</p><p>In 1995, Marie Curie replaced fresh flowers with fabric daffodil pins. Three million were given out and \u00a31.2 million was donated. In 2005, the charity used the term \u2018Great Daffodil Appeal\u2019 for the first time.\n</p><p>In 2011, actress <a href=\"/wiki/Alison_Steadman\" title=\"Alison Steadman\">Alison Steadman</a> appeared in the charity\u2019s first TV advertising campaign for the appeal.  Alison has continued her support for the appeal, appearing in TV ads in 2012,2014 and 2015, as well as the 2016 radio advert with actor <a href=\"/wiki/Dominic_West\" title=\"Dominic West\">Dominic West</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Key_facts\">Key facts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Daffodil_Appeal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Key facts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2014/15, the <a href=\"/wiki/Charitable_organization\" title=\"Charitable organization\">charity</a> provided care to more than 40,700 people with terminal illnesses, and is the largest provider of hospice beds outside the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Health_Service\" title=\"National Health Service\">NHS</a>.\n</p><p>The millions raised by the Great Daffodil Appeal over the years have enabled Marie Curie to provide more free hands-on care to people living with a terminal illness, usually in their own homes or at one of the charity\u2019s <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mariecurie.org.uk/help/hospice-care/hospices\">nine hospices</a>.\n</p><p>During the 2015 Great Daffodil Appeal, more than 22,000 collectors took on 34,000 collections.\n</p><p>As part of the 2016 appeal, supporters are also being encouraged to raise funds by doing something they love, such as hosting a <a href=\"/wiki/Bake_sale\" title=\"Bake sale\">bake sale</a> or quiz night.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Celebrity_supporters\">Celebrity supporters</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Daffodil_Appeal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Celebrity supporters\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Linda_Robson\" title=\"Linda Robson\">Linda Robson</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/The_Saturdays\" title=\"The Saturdays\">The Saturdays</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Jon_Culshaw\" title=\"Jon Culshaw\">Jon Culshaw</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Chuckle_Brothers\" title=\"Chuckle Brothers\">Chuckle Brothers</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Hugh_Grant\" title=\"Hugh Grant\">Hugh Grant</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Chris_Kamara\" title=\"Chris Kamara\">Chris Kamara</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Mangan\" title=\"Stephen Mangan\">Stephen Mangan</a>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Daffodil_Appeal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.mariecurie.org.uk/en-GB/fundraising-volunteering/great-daffodil-appeal/\">http://www.mariecurie.org.uk/en-GB/fundraising-volunteering/great-daffodil-appeal/</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/politics/humza-yousaf-marie-curie-cancer-3238034\">http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/politics/humza-yousaf-marie-curie-cancer-3238034</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Daffodil_Appeal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Marie_Curie\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Marie Curie\">Marie Curie</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mariecurie.org.uk\">Marie Curie  website</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MarieCurieUK\">Great Daffodil Appeal</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Facebook\" title=\"Facebook\">Facebook</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"no